<HEAD>ABC Newsman Peter Jennings Becomes Preacher For Day</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ABC News anchorman Peter Jennings questioned
U.S. defense spending while acting as preacher for a day at
groundbreaking ceremonies for an Episcopal diocesan center.
   ``My question for all of us is: How much are we willing to spend
against the other threats to our life?'' Jennings asked Sunday from
the pulpit of the Cathedral of the Incarnation.
   Jennings noted that Congress was considering a $300 billion
defense appropriation request, but said agencies responsible for
environmental protection, housing or schools received only a
fraction of that amount.
   ``We know God has given us the means to ease the pain, to ease
the suffering,'' Jennings said. ``But somehow we must find the
ingredients to do more, much more.''
   Before his sermon, Jennings joined Episcopal Bishop A. Theodore
Eastman, Mayor Kurt L. Schmoke, the cathedral's dean and two lay
officials. The six used a four-handled silver shovel to turn the
first spade of dirt for the new $4 million center for the Episcopal
Diocese of Maryland.
