<TEXT>
   Stephen King's terrifying ``Pet Sematary''
remained moviegoers' favorite for the second-straight weekend, and
the comedy ``K-9'' made its debut in second place.
   ``Pet Sematary'' earned $8.3 million last weekend and has
brought in more than $24 million in its two weeks of release.
   ``K-9,'' which stars Jim Belushi as a narcotics detective teamed
with a hot shot German shepherd, sold $7.4 million worth of tickets.
   ``Major League'' was in third place with $4.1 million.
   In fourth place was the debut of ``Criminal Law,'' starring Gary
Oldman as a criminal defense attorney who gets client Kevin Bacon
off the hook, then has second thoughts. The movie earned $2.6
million.
