<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0479</SECOND>
<HEAD>Heavy Rains Along East Coast, Cold In Midwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy rain soaked the East Coast and swelled rivers while a cool
Canadian air mass chilled the Midwest.
   Thunderstorms were over eastern North Carolina and eastern
Virginia and rain was widespread in the central Appalachians, the
middle Atlantic Coast states and New England.
   Small stream flood watches were in effect this morning for the
southern and central mountains of Pennsylvania. A flash flood watch
continued from the coast to the foothills of North Carolina.
   Atlanta recorded more than 2} inches of rain on Monday, nearly
doubling the previous rainfall record for the date. Charlotte,
N.C., received more than 1} inches of rain Monday, also setting a
record for the date.
   Greensboro, N.C., received just under 2 inches of rain in the
six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT today, and Florence, S.C., and Key
West, Fla., recorded more than an inch in the same period.
   Rain showers also were scattered across eastern portions of the
Pacific Northwest.
   A cool air mass from Canada settled into the Midwest this
morning, dropping overnight lows into the 30s.
   Today's forecast: widespread rain over New England, New York,
New Jersey and eastern Pennsylvania; showers reaching into the
upper Ohio Valley; showers scattered over Wisconsin, northern
portions of Illinois and Indiana; widely scattered thunderstorms
over southern portions of Florida and Texas; thunderstorms
developing over northwest Texas, western Oklahoma, and the northern
and central Rockies.
   Highs were forecast to be in the upper 40s and 50s from the
Great Lakes and upper Ohio Valley to New England; in the 50s over
western Montana; in the 80s from southern Georgia and Florida
across the Gulf Coast, southern Texas, much of New Mexico and
interior California; and in the 80s and 90s over the Desert
Southwest. The rest of the nation was expectd to have highs in the
60s and 70s.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 28 degrees at Custer,
S.D., to 79 degrees at Blythe, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 57 fair; Boston 45 rain; Buffalo 41 rain;
Charleston, S.C., 68 cloudy; Cincinnati 43 foggy; Cleveland 42
rain; Detroit 46 cloudy; Miami 73 cloudy; New York 52 rain;
Philadelphia 54 rain; Pittsburgh 46 cloudy; Portland, Maine, 44
rain; Washington 61 rain.
   _Central: Bismarck 32 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 56 fair; Denver 51
partly cloudy; Des Moines 36 fair; Indianapolis 46 foggy; Kansas
City 41 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 38 partly cloudy; Nashville 52
fair; New Orleans 67 fair; St. Louis 40 fair.
