<HEAD>Iowa Moved To Anchorage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORFOLK, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The battleship USS Iowa was moved today from
its berth at the Norfolk Naval Station to an anchorage in Hampton
Roads to unload leftover powder and shells from its damaged turret,
a Navy spokesman said.
   The ship had been at a Norfolk pier since it returned to its
home port April 23 after an April 19 explosion that killed 47
sailors in one of the huge gun turrets.
   The ship will spend much of this week at an explosives-handling
berth known as the ``Whiskey'' anchorage, said Lt. Cmdr. John
Lloyd, a spokesman for the Atlantic Fleet's surface forces.
   ``That's safer out there,'' Lloyd said.
   The Navy is investigating the cause of the explosion.
