<FIRST>r i AM-Salvador     05-02 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Salvador,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Die, 13 Injured When Passenger Bus Hits Mine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger bus traveling along
a highway Tuesday ran into a mine, killing two people and injuring
13, officials said.
   The government said the mine was laid by leftist rebels, but the
insurgents blamed the army.
   The vehicle was on a highway about 25 miles northeast of San
Salvador at the time, the army said in a statement. It did not say
how many people were on the bus.
   The military said the mine was planted by rebels from the
Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front.
   The rebels said in a clandestine radio broadcast that the mines
were planted in a military operation designed to keep provincial
residents from reaching the capital for an opposition march.
</TEXT>
