<HEAD>Soldiers Kill 15 Leftist Guerrillas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soldiers on patrol in the Andes encountered a
band of leftist guerrillas and killed 15 in a firefight, the
government said Tuesday.
   A government statement said the battle took place Monday near
Vischongos, 215 miles southeast of Lima in Ayacucho state, and one
soldier also was killed.
   Security forces have reported killing more than 100 guerrillas
in the past month.
   The statement said the soldiers encountered an undetermined
number of guerrillas from the Shining Path, a Maoist group whose
insurgency began in Ayacucho nine years ago, but gave no details.
   Officials say more than 14,000 civilians, rebels, policemen and
soldiers have been killed since the Shining Path began fighting in
1980.
