<FIRST>r a AM-Obit-Williams CORRECTIVE   05-02 0156</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Williams, CORRECTIVE,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: Retransmits to fix date in editors note. Members who used AM-Obit-Williams,
sent as a0725 on April 28 under a Leeton, Mo., dateline, are asked to use
the following story.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LEETON, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press, in an obituary of
former Teamsters President Roy Lee Williams, misidentified James R.
Hoffa as one of the people referred to in a quotation by William J.
McCarthy, the current Teamsters president.
   McCarthy was referring to Roy Lee Williams and to Jackie
Presser, another former Teamsters president, not to Hoffa, when he
said in testimony before the Senate Permanent Subcommittee on
Investigations in Washington April 4, ``One was a cheat and one was
a liar and both were mixed up with La Cosa Nostra by their own
admissions. I didn't care for either one of them.''
   Hoffa, also a former president of the union, disappeared in
1975. McCarthy became president after Presser's death last year.
</TEXT>
