<HEAD>Toll From Hailstorms Reaches 157</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hailstorms that battered wide areas of southwest
Sichuan province killed 157 people and injured 6,000, the China
Daily said Wednesday.
   The storms, which hit 105 of the province's 175 counties from
April 20 through last week, also destroyed 170,000 houses, the
English-language newspaper said.
   Earlier reports had put the death toll from the storms at 87.
   The newspaper said the provincial government is mobilizing all
departments for rescue and relief operations for the
disaster-affected areas.
   Western Sichuan was also hit by two powerful earthquakes last
month that killed at least 11 people.
   The hailstorms were attributed to collisions of warm and cold
fronts. Hail and windstorms also killed seven people in Guizhou
province to the east of Sichuan in late April.
