<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices crept higher in listless trading on Wall
Street today with no substantive news to motivate investors.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 2.20 to 2,417.16
as of noon EDT.
   Advancing issues were ahead of decliners by a margin of about 4
to 3, with 712 issues up, 545 down and 565 unchanged on the New
York Stock Exchange.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 80.22 million shares by midday.
   ``It hasn't done much of anything today,'' said Jack Barbanel, a
market analyst with Gruntal &amp; Co. ``There was some support from
program traders, but the market by itself doesn't have enough
momentum.''
   ``There's not too much propelling the action one way or
another,'' said Dennis Jarrett, an analyst with Kidder, Peabody &amp;
Co.
   Jarrett noted the bond market was tranquil, and although central
banks were intervening in foreign exchange markets and selling
dollars, this development did not seem to affect stock trading.
   The government reported today that sales of new homes fell 5.5
percent in March and that orders to U.S. factories rose 0.7 percent
last month. But Barbanel said the statistics also had little effect
on trading.
   He said the market was unlikely to move with any conviction
until the government issues its unemployment report for April on
Friday.
   The most actively-traded issue on the NYSE was Texaco, down [ to
54[.
   Among other active stocks, Pepsico rose 1[ to 49\ after
announcing its first-quarter earnings.
   Among blue chip issues, General Electric rose \ to 49 while AT&amp;T
was up [ to 34|.
   Ogilvy Group, which soared more than $17 Monday after WPP Group
PLC proposed a $730 million buyout of the advertising concern, was
up a more modest { to 49| in over-the-counter trading.
   Another over-the-counter issue, R.P. Scherer, fell 3\ to 30[
after a Shearson Lehman Hutton Holdings Inc. unit agreed to acquire
the gelatin capsule manufacturer.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
0.22 to 173.04. On the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up 0.17 to 345.45.
