<FIRST>r f BC-AutoGrades     05-02 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Grades,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Gets An `A' From Trade Magazine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RADNOR, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Corp. received a ``A'' for the
second straight year and the nation's two other big automakers also
received overall high marks from a trade magazine Tuesday.
   Automotive Industries, a Chilton Co. publication, gave General
Motors Corp. a B for overall performance, up from a B-minus last
year, and Chrysler received a B minus, up from a C-minus a year ago.
   In assigning the grades in six categories, the magazine
considers a company's change over the previous year rather than
comparing companies.
   Chrysler got the highest mark for quality, an A plus, while GM
got an A and Ford a B plus.
   Chrysler was the only company to get a D in any of the six
areas, receiving the low grade for profit per unit and return on
sales.
   Ford was the only other automaker to get an A plus, receiving
the high mark for U.S. market share and productivity.
</TEXT>
